Vehement/Teufel/Nemesis Enforcer/Scatterblaster:




"Scans have proven ineffective so far." Teufel stated.

"Yes.  But if Lord Unicron says it is here, it is here."

"Of course." Teufel replied, not at all sarcastic.

The Archbishop, still in his ceremonial robes, looked over to Teufel, who 
still looked like an exact duplicate of Zardus.  The Archbishop restrained 
himself from opening fire on Teufel and focused on his mission, his scanners 
going off.  "Two incoming robots, from the faction Alliance."

---

"We're closer, look, there is he!" Nemesis yelled.

"Is he?"

"Shut up!"

"Hey, he's with the Brotherhood.  He's a traitor!" Scatterblaster yelled, 
pulling out his automatic rifle.

"No you idiot, he's a prisoner!  That means Wolfgang has aligned himself with 
the Brotherhood and the Neo 'Cons.  That sick twisted freak!" Nemesis yelled, 
taking out his rapid-firing laser rifle.  "Don't worry, Zardus, we're 
a'comin'!" he yelled, blasting off at full speed, Scatterblaster following.
